         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we study discretizations of the general pantograph equation &lt;tex-math&gt;$y'(t) = ay(t) + by(\theta(t)) + cy'(\phi(t)),\quad t \geq 0,\quad y(0) = y_0,$&lt;/tex-math&gt; where a, b, c, and y&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; are complex numbers and where θ and φ are strictly increasing functions on the nonnegative reals with θ(0) = φ(0) = 0 and &lt;latex&gt;$\theta(t) &lt; t, \phi(t) &lt; t$&lt;/latex&gt; for positive t. Our purpose is an analysis of the stability of the numerical solution with trapezoidal rule discretizations, and we will identify conditions on a, b, c and the stepsize which imply that the solution sequence {y&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n = 0&lt;/sub&gt; is bounded or that it tends to zero algebraically, as a negative power of n.</p>
          </abstract>
